      "title": "The Brain and Neurons",
      "description": "The brain is made up of billions of tiny cells called neurons. Neurons communicate with each other using electrical and chemical signals. These signals travel very fast and allow us to react, think, and process information.\n\nWhen you see something, hear a sound, or touch something hot, neurons send messages through the nervous system to your brain. The brain then processes this information and tells your body how to respond.",
